tweet: On 8 April, 1929, Bhagat Singh and Batukeshwar Dutt had hurled a bomb and showered leaflets in Delhi Assembly. The idea was to make the deaf hear and rouse the people against colonial rule. Today let us salute them by intensifying the #RepealFarmLaws and #SaveDemocracy movement.  https://t.co/NEa3Izr6yL
